ne}} [[2005 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship Division B|2005]]||6th\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Romania}} [[2006 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship Division B|2006]]||14th\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Bulgaria}} [[2007 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship Division B|2007]]||14th\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Hungary}} [[2008 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship Division B|2008]]||9th\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Bosnia and Herzegovina}} [[2009 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship Division B|2009]]||11th\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Israel}} [[2010 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship Division B|2010]]||12th\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Bulgaria}} [[2011 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship Division B|2011]]||6th\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Bosnia and Herzegovina}} [[2012 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship Division B|2012]]||9th\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Macedonia}} [[2013 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship Division B|2013]]||8th\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Bulgaria}} [[2014 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship Division B|2014]]||13th\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Austria}} [[2015 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship Division B|2015]]||11th\n|- \n|{{flagicon|Macedonia}} [[2016 FIBA U18 European Championship Division B|2016]]||17th\n|-  \n|{{flagicon|Estonia}} [[2017 FIBA U18 European Championship Division B|2017]]||6th\n|- bgcolor=gold\n|{{flagicon|Macedonia}} [[2018 FIBA U18 European Championship Division B|2018]]||'''1st'''\n|- \n|{{flagicon|Romania}} [[2019 FIBA U18 European Championship Division B|2019]]||rowspan=1|''Did not participate''\n|-     \n!Total!!14/15\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Individual awards==\n*'''Under-18 Championship Division B MVP'''\n**[[Nathan Kuta]] \u2013 [[2018 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship Division B|2018]]\n\n==See also==\n*[[Netherlands national basketball team]]\n*[[Netherlands national under-17 basketball team]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.basketball.nl/ Official website] {{in lang|nl}}\n*[http://www.fiba.basketball/federation/Netherlands FIBA profile]\n\n{{International youth basketball}}\n{{National sports teams of the Netherlands}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Netherlands national under-19 basketball team}}\n[[Category:Basketball in the Netherlands]]\n[[Category:Basketball teams in the Netherlands]]\n[[Category:National under-18 basketball teams]]\n[[Category:National under-19 basketball teams]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox national basketball team\n| country            = Netherlands \n| logo               = Flag of Netherlands.svg\n| logo_width         = 130px \n| nickname           = Orange Lions\n| fiba_zone          = FIBA Europe\n| national_fed       = [[Basketball Nederland]]\n| coach              = [[Paul Vervaeck]]\n| wc_championship    = [[FIBA Under-19 Basketball World Cup|Under-19 World Cup]]\n| wc_appearances     = None \n| wc_medals          = \n| zone_championship  = [[FIBA U18 European Championship|U18 European Championship]]\n| zone_appearances   = 5\n| zone_medals        = None\n| zone_championship2 = [[FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship Division B|U18 European Championship Division B]]\n| zone_appearances2  = 14\n| zone_medals2       = {{Eur1}} ''Gold:'' ([[2018 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship Division B|2018]])\n| h_body             = FF5800\n| h_title            = Home\n| h_pattern_b        = _black_nzfc_shoulders\n| h_shorts           = FF5800\n| h_pattern_s        = \n| a_title            = Away\n| a_body             = FFFFFF\n| a_pattern_b        =  _black_nzfc_shoulders\n| a_shorts           = FFFFFF\n| a_pattern_s        = \n}}\n\nThe '''Netherlands national under-18 and under-19 basketball team''' is the national junior [[basketball]] team that represents the [[Netherlands]] in international under-18 and under-19 (under age 19 and under age 18) tournaments.<ref>{{cite web|title=Netherlands (U18-U19)|url=https://www.eurobasket.com/Holland/basketball-National-Team.asp?Age=18|accessdate=6 November 2019}}</ref> The team is governed by [[Basketball Nederland]]. The current coach is [[Paul Vervaeck]].\n\nIn 2018, the team won its first medal when it won gold at the [[2018 FIBA U18 European Championship Division B]] tournament.<ref name=\"FIBA.basketball 2018\">{{cite web | title=Netherlands celebrate historic title in Skopje | website=FIBA.basketball | date= | url=http://www.fiba.basketball/europe/u18b/2018/news/netherlands-celebrate-historic-title-in-skopje | access-date=5 August 2018}}</ref> Following their victory, the Netherlands were promoted to Division A.\n\n==Competitive record==\n{{col-begin|width=auto}}\n{{col-break}}\n===U18 European Championship===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"   \n|-\n!Year\n!width=\"100\"|Position\n|- \n|{{flagicon|Italy}} [[1964 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship|1964]]||rowspan=5|''Did not participate''\n|- \n|{{flagicon|Italy}} [[1966 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship|1966]]\n|- \n|{{flagicon|Spain|1945}} [[1968 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship|1968]]\n|- \n|{{flagicon|Greece}} [[1970 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship|1970]]\n|- \n|{{flagicon|Yugoslavia}} [[1972 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship|1972]]\n|- \n|{{flagicon|France}} [[1974 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship|1974]]||12th\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Spain|1945}} [[1976 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship|1976]]||rowspan=5|''Did not participate''\n|- \n|{{flagicon|Italy}} [[1978 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship|1978]]\n|- \n|{{flagicon|Yugoslavia}} [[1980 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship|1980]]\n|- \n|{{flagicon|Bulgaria|1971}} [[1982 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship|1982]]\n|- \n|{{flagicon|Sweden}} [[1984 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship|1984]]\n|- \n|{{flagicon|Austria}} [[1986 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship|1986]]||11th\n|- \n|{{flagicon|Yugoslavia}} [[1988 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship|1988]]||12th\n|- \n|{{flagicon|Netherlands}} [[1990 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship|1990]]||10th \n|- \n|{{flagicon|Hungary}} [[1992 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship|1992]]||rowspan=7|''Did not participate''\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Israel}} [[1994 FIBA Europe Under-18 Championship|1994]]\n|-\n|{{flagicon|France}} [[1996 FIBA Europe Under-18 Champion